Suggestion: Implement Subclass Relationship Check
We can implement a subclass relationship check in the _narrow function to ensure that the subclass is a subtype of the current class. This can be done by using the isAssignableFrom method in Java. If the subclass is not a subtype of the current class, we can throw an IllegalArgumentException. The modified code would look like this:

```java
protected JavaType _narrow(Class<?> subclass) {
    if (_class == subclass) {
        return this;
    }
    if (!_class.isAssignableFrom(subclass)) {
        throw new IllegalArgumentException("Class " + subclass.getName() + " not sub-type of " + _class.getName());
    }
    return new SimpleType(subclass, _bindings, this, _superInterfaces, _valueHandler, _typeHandler, _asStatic);
}
```
